Wyshbone dev servers (backend + UI)

This project has:

npm run dev → backend (Node/Express) using tsx watch server/index.ts

npm run dev:ui → frontend (Vite on port 5173)

npm run dev:all → runs both concurrently.

Assume that during development, I will start npm run dev:all once and leave it running.

When you change backend or shared code, do NOT tell me “Stop the backend and run npm run dev again.” The watcher will reload automatically.

Only if there are clear errors that require a restart (e.g. the terminal is dead or ports are not listening), you may:

Open the Terminal,

Suggest this single command:

npm run dev:all

In that case, write the command yourself in the terminal and just ask me to click “Run”, instead of asking me what to type.---
